          soothing of lofi music while either setting up my servers or
          developing something out of curiosity, with a cup of tea on my desk ‚òï
        </p>

        <h4>Background</h4>
        <p>
          I was born in Mar del Plata, Argentina, a city know for its turistic
          location, most people come here in the summer, but during most the
          year it is very cold!
        </p>
        <p>
          Growing up, I was known as the 'computer' kid üñ•Ô∏è, I always enjoyed
          being alone on my room and playing around with computers, I was into
          creating interactive animations with Adobe Flash, and later creating
          Desktop programs for Windows XP using Microsoft Visual Basic 6.0
        </p>
        <p>
          As time moved on, I started taking programming more seriously, when I
          was 14 years-old, I joined a local course at my local university about
          üåê Website development with PHP and MySQL.
        </p>
        <p>
          Of course, while setting up Apache on my laptop for development I
          found joy in using Linux and open-source software üêß, I would also
          meet people to discuss operative systems and distributions.
        </p>
        <p>
          When I turned 18-years old, I started working professionally as a
          software developer, through my carrer I used multiple programming
          languages such as C#, PHP, SQL, JavaScript and lately TypeScript.
        </p>

        <p>
          During my free time, I learned Docker, Python, C and Go, just by
          playing around with toy projects: a port scanner, a video shuffler
          from an scrapped database, a RAG-enabled chat bot or simpley a discord
          bot. You name it ü§ì
        </p>

        <p>
          Right now, sitting at my 30 years-old, I focus my expertise in Web
          development while keeping a strong curiosity for other domains. üîç
        </p>

        <h4>Hobbies</h4>
        <p>
          As you might know, I enjoy computer programming a lot, as this
          experimentation time is both entertaining and plays an important role
          in my learning.
        </p>
        <p>
          We can also check the fact that I like using Linux and setting up
          servers that runs anything I want on them.
        </p>
        <p>
          I also like to explore the ethical usage of LLM, I believe that it has
          a lot of potential for different tasks! My favorites are creating
          stories and characters.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of computers, I like watching Movies, Cartoons and listening
          to music! Ranging from Pop, Electronic to Heavy Metal. üé∂
        </p>

